    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#letronne1848"/>, n. <citedRange>i</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl> <ptr target="#CIG"/>, vol. <citedRange>IV</citedRange>, p. <citedRange>1241</citedRange>, <citedRange>5362b</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#froehner1865"/>, n. <citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#jmr1978"/>, n <citedRange>14</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>114700</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#serresjacquart2001"/>, p. <citedRange>416</citedRange>, fig. 11</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#hamiaux-zagdoun2004"/><citedRange/></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2012c"/>, p. <citedRange>149-150</citedRange>, fig. 5</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl-maffre2012"/></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/> <citedRange>68.1746</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-61885"><name nymRef="#Πραξικράτης">Πραξικράτης</name> 
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-61886"><name nymRef="#Ἐπαμείνων" type="patronymic">Ἐπαμείνονο<unclear>ς</unclear></name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλλωνι</name></persName> 
                    <lb n="4"/><w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Praxikratès fils d'Epameinôn <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied> à Apollon au titre de la dîme.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Praxikrates son of Epameinon <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> to Apollo as a tithe.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Praxikrates figlio di Epameinon <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> ad Apollo come decima.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The number 5362b given to the stone in the Addenda of <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/></bibl>  at volume IV had already been given in Volume III to the inscription 
                    which is our <ref type="inscription" source="#GVCyr2">GVCyr05</ref>.</p>
                <p>The stone was thought lost by Reynolds who included it into the collection of Berenike; however, the lettering shows clearly that it antedates the foundation of 
                    Berenike and should come from Euesperides. About the present condition of the stone, a paper by C. Dobias-Lalou has been given to press for Bulletin de la Société 
                    Nationale des Antiquaires de France, year 2012, unfortunately not yet published.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
